import numpy as np

Notes on the Assignment¶

I thought of two ways to correct the notebook. First, the way that is presented here, changing the mean on the kt3dn par file. In this approach the nscore variables are just used to model the standardized variogram.

Other approach would be to krig the nscore values and then back transform the estimates. Since the first approach worked fine I chosed to present it.

            tmin=gs.Parameters['data.tmin'],

In [15]:
x_range = np.ptp(dfl[dfl.x].values)
y_range = np.ptp(dfl[dfl.y].values) 
n_lag_x =  np.ceil((x_range * 0.5) /  lag_length_h) 
n_lag_y =  np.ceil((y_range * 0.5) /  lag_length_h)
lag_tol_h = lag_length_h * 0.6

parstr = """      Parameters for VARCALC
                  **********************

90.0 15 1000 0.0 22.5 1000 0.0   -Dir 02: azm,azmtol,bandhorz,dip,diptol,bandvert,tilt

                                  n_directions = n_directions,

                                  lag_length_h = lag_length_h,

             liveoutput=True)
